"title": "6617: atonement, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6617: atonement, in nt",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In dying for the sins of the world, Jesus Christ fulfilled and replaced the OT sacrificial system, so that all who believe in him are restored to fellowship with God. Christ is the true high priest, who finally liberates his people from the guilt of sin, by offering himself as the supreme sacrifice.</p>\n<h2>The atoning purpose of Jesus Christ's death</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's death on behalf of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:14-John10:18\">JHN 10:14–10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:15\">2CO 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:9\">HEB 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:16\">1JN 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's atoning death for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3\">1CO 15:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:25\">ROM 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:4\">GAL 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>The atoning significance of Jesus Christ's death is expressed by references to his blood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:9\">ROM 5:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:13\">EPH 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:14\">REV 7:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's atoning death is commemorated in the Lord's Supper</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:23–11:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:26–26:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:22–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:19–22:20</a></p>\n<h2>Explanations of the atonement</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's death as an atoning sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:7\">1CO 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:2\">EPH 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:10\">1JN 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6\">REV 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's atoning death as redemption</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13-Gal3:14\">GAL 3:13–3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:13-Col1:14\">COL 1:13–1:14</a></p>\n<h2>The atonement is effective because of Jesus Christ's sinlessness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22-1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:22–2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:5\">1JN 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's death fulfils and replaces the Day of Atonement</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ makes atonement as the new high priest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26-Heb7:28\">HEB 7:26–7:28</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the mediator of the new and better covenant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:6-Heb8:7\">HEB 8:6–8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ has made atonement in the true heavenly sanctuary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1-Heb8:2\">HEB 8:1–8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24\">HEB 9:24</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's atoning blood brings effective cleansing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12-Heb9:14\">HEB 9:12–9:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's single sacrifice replaces the many required under the old covenant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:11-Heb10:14\">HEB 10:11–10:14</a></p>\n<h3>Access to the heavenly sanctuary is now open</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:20\">HEB 10:19–10:20</a></p>\n<h2>By dying with Christ, believers are released from this age into the life of the age to come</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:7\">ROM 6:1–6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:4-Rom7:6\">ROM 7:4–7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:19-Gal2:20\">GAL 2:19–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:14\">GAL 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:6-Eph2:7\">EPH 2:6–2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:11-Col2:13\">COL 2:11–2:13</a></p>\n<h2>God the Father and the atoning death of his Son</h2>\n<h3>God's sending of his Son to make atonement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:14\">1JN 4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:32\">ROM 8:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18\">2CO 5:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h3>God's grace displayed in making atonement for the ungodly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4-Eph2:5\">EPH 2:4–2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6-Rom5:8\">ROM 5:6–5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8-Eph2:9\">EPH 2:8–2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:4-Titus3:5\">TIT 3:4–3:5</a></p>\n<h2>The worldwide scope of Jesus Christ's atoning death</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:2\">1JN 2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5\">1TI 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>The appropriate response to the atonement</h2>\n<h3>The response of repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:19\">ACT 3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:30\">ACT 17:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:21\">ACT 20:21</a></p>\n<h3>The response of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:43\">ACT 10:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:14-John3:15\">JHN 3:14–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:31\">ACT 16:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:22\">ROM 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:16\">GAL 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>The response of baptism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:16\">ACT 22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:21</a></p>",
